This page is the Detailed Analysis section of the dashboard. While the previous page showed the "Big Picture," this one is for looking at specific details to understand why things are happening.

Here is a breakdown in simple words:

1. Detailed Lists (The "Who and What")
This page likely features a large table. Instead of just showing a total number of patients, it lists them individually. You can see:

Patient Names (or ID numbers).

Admission Dates: Exactly when they arrived.

Assigned Doctors: Who is responsible for their care.

Status: Whether they are waiting, in treatment, or ready to leave.

2. Slicers and Filters (The "Sorting Hats")
On the side or top, there are small menus (Slicers) that let you change the whole view with one click. You can filter the data by:

Specific Ward: Only see patients in the ICU.

Specific Doctor: See only the patients assigned to Dr. Smith.

Date Range: Look at data from just last weekend.

3. Comparison Charts
You will see charts that compare different groups. For example:

Emergency vs. Planned: How many people came in as an emergency versus those who had an appointment.

Age Groups: Are most of the patients children, adults, or seniors?

4. Performance Metrics
This part of the dashboard often tracks efficiency. It shows things like:

Average Stay: How many days a patient typically spends in the hospital.

Treatment Costs: A look at the expenses for different types of care.
